Ready to write the best chapter of your career? XSELL Technologies leverages artificial intelligence as a foundational capability to listen, learn and support agents in real time with the exact information they need to exceed customers‚Äô expectations and deliver top performer experiences. 
Join us on our mission to empower agents, clients and organizations to increase human performance and job satisfaction through making conversations more personal. We do this by pairing together the best elements of human touch and machine intelligence to drive results. 
XSELL is currently seeking an Scrum Master to be responsible for designing practices, processes, procedures and systems to manage work simply and effectively. This person will seek to understand business needs, collaborate with key stakeholders, apply different strategies to convince others to change their opinion or plan, and win support from others for ideas. 
What You Will Bring 
The problems you will tackle will benefit from the following skills: 
3+ years of experience as a Scrum Master 
Strong knowledge and experience using Jira 
Excellent knowledge of Scrum techniques and artifacts (such as definition of done, user stories, automated testing, backlog refinement) 
Good knowledge of other Agile frameworks (Crystal, XP etc.) 
Excellent communication and team focused leadership skills 
Degree in Computer Science, Business or similar field 
Scrum master certification is a plus 
Ways You Will Contribute 
Lead the team in using Agile methodology and scrum practices 
Drives scrum team ceremonies (e.g. daily stand-up, backlog grooming, sprint planning, sprint review, retrospective) 
Resolves impediments impacting team's ability to deliver business value 
Tracks dependencies and risks for team delivery 
Provides leadership, direction and coaching to scrum teams 
Maintains metrics that provide visibility to stakeholders on team-level maturity, plans, progress and quality 
Facilitate internal communication and effective collaboration 
Monitor and improve performance of all team members involved in delivery. 
Responsible for ensuring Scrum is understood and the team adheres to Scrum theory, practice, and guidelines. 
Helps the product team and development team to achieve customer satisfaction 
Maintaining a positive, self-motivated, can-do attitude. 
Demonstrating strong leadership and team-building skills by creating an atmosphere of cooperation and cohesiveness. 
Guide development teams to higher scrum maturity 
Help build a productive environment where team members ‚Äòown‚Äô the product and enjoy working on it. 
What To Expect In Your First 30 Days 
Meet with everyone on the Technology and Product teams 
Meet relevant business stakeholders 
Learn the products and organization structure 
Review existing roadmaps and/or project plans 
Review two sprint cycles (2 week sprints) 
Begin to assemble dashboards for Scrum metrics 
